TITLE: Biden saying 'Don't' and other threats seemingly fail to deter Iran as more US Mideast bases hit
SUMMARY: President Biden once again said his message to Iran was "Don't" when asked about its anticipated response against Israel. Critics say the lack of action against Tehran only emboldens the regime.

TITLE: Turkey's invasion threats should be taken 'very seriously': Cyprus official
SUMMARY: Turkey invaded part of Cyprus in 1974 and claimed it as an independent territory for the Turkish ethnic population, going on to rename areas of the island and destroy historical sites.

TITLE: US, UK and Australia take next step in integrating AI defense systems
SUMMARY: The U.S., U.K. and Australia expanded their ability to integrate unmanned aerial vehicles with emerging AI technology to bolster joint defenses against adversaries like China.

TITLE: King Charles lauds ‘resilience’ over ‘aggression’ in riots after criticism he didn't condemn UK unrest sooner
SUMMARY: King Charles III spoke out against rioting that enveloped the nation for more than a week on Saturday after he faced criticism for not condemning the violence sooner.

TITLE: Pilot, 35, identified from Brazil plane that spiraled out of sky and crashed, killing 62
SUMMARY: Capt. Danilo Santos Romano, 35, was identified as the pilot in the fatal Brazilian air disaster that killed all 62 people who were on board.

TITLE: Teenager going for a quick swim severely injured in shark attack
SUMMARY: A 15-year-old from Colorado was severely injured when a shark attacked her while she was swimming on a family vacation in Belize this week.

TITLE: Passenger plane crashes in Brazil, killing all people on board, airline VoePass says
SUMMARY: A plane operated by the Brazilian airline VoePass has crashed in the country's Sao Paulo state on Friday, reports say.

TITLE: US assets deployed to Mideast will help Israel but will unlikely alter Iran's mind on retaliation, experts say
SUMMARY: The U.S. has deployed a dozen warships in recent months to the Middle East, diminishing the need for heavy redeployment of assets because the Navy maintains a robust presence in the region.

TITLE: Would-be VoePass passengers say they missed doomed Brazilian flight over booking mix-up
SUMMARY: Two would-be passengers say they cheated death on Friday after a mix-up resulted in them missing their flight aboard the doomed VoePass airliner which crashed in Brazil and killing all 62 people on board.

TITLE: Putin under pressure as Ukraine incursion continues, may give Kyiv bargaining chips in peace talks: experts
SUMMARY: The incursions into Russian territory might allow Ukraine to retake some territory as Moscow shifts its forces, but one expert argued the attack could strengthen Putin, too.

TITLE: Taylor Swift terror plot: Neighbors in main suspect's hometown describe changes in his behavior
SUMMARY: Locals in Ternitz, Austria are now describing changes in the recent behavior of the main suspect in an alleged terrorist plot to attack Taylor Swift concerts.

TITLE: Hezbollah is the 'X-factor' in looming Israel, Iran war with 'nation state capabilities'
SUMMARY: As the world waits to see if Iran will act out its threats against Israel, a former Israeli Defense Forces official is sounding the alarm that the bigger threat could be sitting on Israel's doorstep: Hezbollah.

TITLE: Venezuela's Maduro bans X for 10 days following exchange with Elon Musk
SUMMARY: Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro ordered a 10-day ban on access to X in his country after a heated exchange with its owner Elon Musk following the country's presidential election.

TITLE: Ukraine brings war to Russia in ‘massive’ drone strike on military, government targets
SUMMARY: Ukraine launched a 'massive' drone strike across at least five Russian regions as its troops advance further into Russia's Kursk region in an apparent effort to draw forces away from the front lines.

TITLE: UK government warns 'think before you post' amid threats to arrest citizens for offensive rhetoric on socials
SUMMARY: The United Kingdom government warned citizens to "think before your post," threatening jail time for individuals posting offensive messages amid anti-immigration riots across the nation.

TITLE: US issues warning to Iran of 'serious risk' if it carries out retaliatory attack against Israel: report
SUMMARY: The U.S. has reportedly warned Iran that a retaliatory attack on Israel for the recent killing of a Hamas leader in Tehran would pose a “serious risk" to the country's stability.

TITLE: Catalan separatist Puigdemont evades capture on chaotic return to Spain
SUMMARY: Carles Puigdemont, a former Catalan separatist leader, defied an arrest warrant and appeared at a Barcelona rally; he allegedly left the vicinity in a car belonging to a police officer.

TITLE: Britain remains on alert for further unrest, even after anti-racism campaigners face down far right
SUMMARY: After a week of anti-immigrant violence across the U.K., British authorities said they are preparing for possible further unrest and applauded the efforts of police and anti-racism campaigners.

TITLE: Israel issues message to Lebanese citizens amid reports of potential preemptive strike on Hezbollah
SUMMARY: Hezbollah lost two high-ranking commanders in the span of a week, giving the group greater cause to strike at Israel, whom they hold responsible for the assassinations.

TITLE: Justice Department indicts Iranian, Pakistani nationals linked to Navy SEAL deaths in Arabian Sea
SUMMARY: The Justice Department has indicted two Iranians and a Pakistani national over their alleged support of Iran’s weapons of mass destruction program.

TITLE: Fighting rages inside Russian territory after Ukraine's surprise incursion
SUMMARY: Thousands of civilians have evacuated from Russia's Kursk region following Ukraine's surprise invasion as Moscow reportedly struggles to hold ground even as Kyiv sees mounting losses.

TITLE: US ambassador to Japan to skip Nagasaki A-bomb memorial service because Israel was excluded
SUMMARY: The U.S., EU and five other G-7 nations said they will send lower-ranked envoys instead of ambassadors to this year's atomic bombing memorial in Nagasaki because Israel was excluded.

TITLE: 7.1 magnitude earthquake strikes off Japan's coast, tsunami advisory issued
SUMMARY: A magnitude 7.1 earthquake was detected off Japan's southern coast, triggering a tsunami advisory. No injuries or serious damage were immediately reported.

TITLE: Polish man sentenced to four months, deported from Denmark for June assault on Danish prime minister
SUMMARY: A Polish man has been sentenced to 4 months in jail for punching Danish Prime Minister Mette Frederiksen in the shoulder; the man also confessed to separate charges including sexual harassment.

TITLE: Egypt asks its airlines to avoid Iran airspace for three hours on Thursday
SUMMARY: Amid tension between Iran and Israel, Egypt has instructed its airlines to avoid Iran's airspace for several hours in the morning on Thursday; military exercises will reportedly be conducted.
